structured.description: A constant function named `fn` that is declared using an arrow function syntax. The function executes by logging the integer value 0 to the console using the `console.log()` method. The result of this operation is the output of the value 0 in the console.

items.description: Logs a value of 0 to the console when invoked. It is a constant arrow function that does not take any arguments and immediately calls `console.log` with the argument 0.
items.name: fn
